<br>
The fact of the matter is, the Pope is a religious leader.  It is his duty to instill hope in the hearts of his followers - in all the world.  The Pope spoke of peace, of love, but he knows that to get to this will require force.<br>
<br>
I am not arguing with the idea of peace.  I would love nothing more than for the terrorists of the world to come out, give up, and stop their evil ways.  The reality of the matter is, though, that this will not happen.  Something must be done to ensure that this never happens again.  Human life is a prescious thing, and hatred does nothing but fuel the fires of the terrorist groups.  There is no way to bargain.  There is no way to convert them.  There is no way to work out a deal.  When a person has been alive as long as his Holiness has, he knows the ways of the world.  He knows what will happen, and he mourns it, but I am sure he also knows it is necessary to ensure the safety and freedom of the people of the world.<br>
<br>
These terrorists must be eradicated, for the good of people everywhere.  Peace and freedom are not free... they are paid for in blood.  Sad though it is, it is true.<br>
