I hope you are not serious.  The Pope has NEVER spoke out for violence, hate nor blood.  Do not put your own opinions into his statement, read his words, and his words only.<br>
<br>
I have quoted to prove my point:<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> I add my voice to all the voices raised in these hours to express indignant condemnation, and I strongly reiterate that the ways of violence will never lead to genuine solutions to humanity's problems.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Even if the forces of darkness appear to prevail, those who believe in God know that evil and death do not have the final say. <hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
