<!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><b><i>Quote:</i></b><hr> Let us beg the Lord that the spiral of hatred and violence will not prevail. May the Blessed Virgin, Mother of Mercy, fill the hearts of all with wise thoughts and peaceful intentions.<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END--><br>
<br>
Let us not assume that the Pope says one thing while he believes something else, until you can prove he believes in something else.  <br>
<br>
No mention of force or blood there, nor violence or hate.<br>
He is speaking AGAINST violence and hate.  Feel free to disagree with him, but do not assume he does not truly believe what he says.<br>
<br>
Its very ironic how the eigth grader's opinion is disregarded because of his age/naivity, and the Pope's statement gets new meanings added because he is old and wise.<br>
<br>
Do you really think because you read 100 people who come here to say violence is the answer that anyone esle in this world over a certain age AUTOMATICALLY agree because they are old and wise and everyone under a certain age does not know better because they are young and naive?<br>
<br>
I truly hope not, and would hope you would take a person;s word rather than discrediting it based on age or assuming they meant something else based on age.  I bet if an eigth grader wrote about how he wants to see boodshed and revenge, he would not be called naive.<br>
<br>
Sad state of affairs.  I am done with this thread.  Every time I read this message board I am reminded how the terrorists have already won.  Go and kill them all, every terrorist in the world, kill them ded.  They still won.<br>
